Reasoning: 
1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper analyzes the expected time complexity of the auction algorithm and the push relabel algorithm for maximal bipartite matching on random graphs. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the time complexity of algorithms for the matching problem on bipartite graphs. This is a core topic in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses concepts from information theory to analyze the expected time complexity of the auction algorithm. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the implementation of the auction algorithm on parallel machines, which involves numerical analysis techniques. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the implementation of the auction algorithm on parallel machines with shared memory, which falls under the scope of distributed and parallel computing.
